=== DELEGATING TO CLAUDE CODE ===
Project: claudetrack
Task: Fix two critical issues:

## Issue 1: Auth flow bug
- If user is already logged in, 'Start Free Trial' and 'Get Started' buttons should go to /dashboard NOT /auth/signup
- In src/app/page.tsx: pricing buttons and hero CTA must check auth state
  - Solution: make the landing page check Supabase session server-side, pass isLoggedIn prop to client component
  - If logged in: buttons → /dashboard
  - If not logged in: buttons → /auth/signup

## Issue 2: Real tracking mechanism
ClaudeTrack tracks AI coding usage by parsing ~/.claude/stats-cache.json which Claude Code writes automatically.

The stats-cache.json contains:
- modelUsage: per-model token counts (inputTokens, outputTokens, cacheReadInputTokens, cacheCreationInputTokens, costUSD)
- dailyActivity: per-day session counts
- dailyModelTokens: per-day per-model token breakdown

Build a tracker CLI agent that users install:

1. Create src/app/api/ingest/route.ts
   - POST endpoint accepting: { model, inputTokens, outputTokens, cacheReadTokens, costUSD, date, projectName }
   - Requires Authorization: Bearer <api_key> header
   - Saves to Supabase sessions table

2. Create a tracker script at public/install/tracker.sh
   - Users run: curl -s https://claudetrack.qucord.com/install/tracker.sh | bash
   - Script installs to ~/.claudetrack/tracker.sh
   - Adds cron: */5 * * * * to run every 5 min
   - Reads ~/.claude/stats-cache.json
   - Diffs from last run (store last state in ~/.claudetrack/last_state.json)
   - POSTs diff to https://claudetrack.qucord.com/api/ingest with user's API key

3. Add API key management to dashboard
   - src/app/dashboard/page.tsx: add 'API Key' section showing user's key
   - API key = Supabase user id (simple approach for MVP)
   - Show install command: curl -s https://claudetrack.qucord.com/install/tracker.sh | bash -s -- <api_key>

4. Update dashboard to show REAL data from sessions table

Also remove Google OAuth button from login/signup pages (only GitHub + email)

Run bun run build and fix all errors.

